Plans

The plans were submitted in two phases: one for the Permitted Development Certificate for the Loft Conversion, which was submitted in August and approved in October 2022; the second one for the Planning Permission for the Front Extension, submitted in November 2022 and approved in January 2023.

The loft hip-to-gable conversion will accommodate a master bedroom with a window on the back, which will have nice views over the garden and the park, plus two Velux window on the section with a sloped ceiling (under the roof). There will also be an en-suite bathroom, bigger than the one on the first floor, with a window with obsured glazing.

On the first floor, the staircase will have to go in what was Luca’s bedroom and the door will be moved back about a metre. However, the room will be extended to the front by about 1.20m, so it will actually become slightly bigger. Definitely big enough for a study with a desk and bookshelp and we could easily put in a sofa bed too. The current master bedroom door will have to move back to make room for the landing, so the room will become slightly smaller.

On the ground floor, the front porch will be replaced by a bigger hallway. There will only be one door – the main front door – so the space will be used more effectively and hopefully we will have more space to store coats and shoes. We will need to find a solution for deliveries though, as the front porch was very useful for that.
